id: pm-7ob5
title: "Graph analytics for planning and context: critical paths, blast radius, bottlenecks, communities, redundancy, and explainable relevance signals"
description: "Implement deterministic, incremental, and explainable algorithms that turn typed relationship data into planning decisions and token-efficient context signals."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 2
tags[7]: algorithms,"area:context","area:graph",context-management,performance,planning,scale
created_at: "2026-07-13T21:58:35.029Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-14T11:19:56.297Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 900
acceptance_criteria: "Order-bearing DAG analysis provides topological order, critical path, slack, prerequisite depth, frontier, dominators, and transitive reduction while reporting genuine cycles separately; Impact analysis provides reverse reachability, bounded blast radius, articulation points or bridges, dependency fan-in and fan-out, bottlenecks, and change-risk propagation; Knowledge-graph analysis provides connected components, strongly connected components by edge family, community detection, centrality, redundancy, structural holes, and orphan classification; Algorithms are exact where bounded and expose deterministic approximation method, seed, error or confidence bounds, freshness, and omitted counts otherwise; Incremental and temporal variants consume immutable history and support snapshot comparison, trend, change-point, and counterfactual what-if analysis; Each signal includes provenance and a concise explanation suitable for context packing; no opaque score is authoritative by itself; Evaluation compares quality, latency, memory, update cost, and token savings on scratch, medium, adversarial, multi-decade, and one-million-item fixtures"
goal: project management = context management
objective: Derive actionable project and context intelligence from typed graphs without conflating associative and order-bearing relationships
value: "Agents and maintainers can find critical work, impact, bottlenecks, communities, missing links, and the best bounded context automatically"
impact: "Improves prioritization, change safety, duplicate avoidance, context relevance, and portfolio understanding from tiny to million-item trackers"
outcome: "A library of snapshot-aware graph analytics with explanations, incremental updates, approximation bounds, and evaluation evidence"
why_now: The context engine already plans multi-signal scoring but needs trustworthy graph semantics and scalable derived features
parent: pm-96h7
risk: high
confidence: medium
